From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bruno Castelló <bfcastello@gmail.com>
Date: TBD
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] drivers/vga: inject vgpu3d properties into ATI PCI node

STATUS: STUB — NOT applied in CI.  le-l@ is a runtime-only word bound
via bind_func() in libopenbios/init.c; the FCode tokenizer (toke/fcode-utils)
does not have it in its dictionary and will error.  Must be rewritten using
tokenizer-safe words (e.g. two le-w@ calls) before applying.  See PATCHES.md.

This patch documents the planned
OpenBIOS Forth change that detects the vgpu3d transport layer in the
ATI Rage 128 Pro device node and injects the properties that allow the
Mac OS 9 guest extension to discover 3D acceleration capability at boot
without performing its own MMIO probe.

--- MOTIVATION ---

The guest System Extension (sources/ATIAccel.c) performs its own magic
check at VGPU3D_CTRL_OFFSET+0x08 after mapping BAR2.  This OpenBIOS
patch is therefore not strictly required for correctness, but it provides
two advantages:

  1. Clean device-tree contract: classic Mac OS drivers expect capability
     flags in the Name Registry tree rather than side-channel MMIO probes.
     Injecting "qemu,vgpu3d" lets any NameRegistry-aware code discover
     the accelerator without touching MMIO at startup.

  2. Futureproofing: OpenBIOS is the right place to gate on whether the
     host QEMU binary actually supports vgpu3d (magic read succeeds only
     when hw/display/ati.c has patch 0003 applied).  If the guest is
     booted on a vanilla QEMU build the property is simply absent and the
     extension falls back gracefully to 2D.

--- IMPLEMENTATION NOTES ---

  Control register magic is at: mmio-addr + VGPU3D_CTRL_OFFSET + REG_MAGIC
    = mmio-addr + h#4000 + h#08
    = mmio-addr + h#4008

  le-l@ (defined in libopenbios/init.c as __le32_to_cpu(*aaddr)) is the
  correct word for reading a 32-bit little-endian value from MMIO on a
  big-endian PowerPC guest.  The vgpu3d control registers are declared
  DEVICE_LITTLE_ENDIAN in ati.c; QEMU byte-swaps the handler return value
  for the big-endian CPU, and le-l@ byte-swaps again, restoring the
  correct value.  The magic constant is 0x56475033 ("VGP3").

  After map-mmio completes (mmio-addr is valid) and vbe-init has run,
  the new block:
    * reads mmio-addr + h#4008 via le-l@
    * if it equals h#56475033, reads the version at mmio-addr + h#400C
    * installs two properties into the current device node:
        "qemu,vgpu3d"        (string "true")
        "qemu,vgpu3d-ver"    (integer, protocol version number)

  These properties appear in the ATY,Rage128Pd Name Registry node and
  are visible to GetNamedProperty() calls from the guest extension.

  NOTE: Until QEMU patches 0003/0004 are committed, le-l@ at h#4008
  returns 0 (falls through to ati_mm_read default), the if branch is
  not taken, and no properties are injected.  This is the safe fallback.

Signed-off-by: Bruno Castelló <bfcastello@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/vga.fs | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/vga.fs b/drivers/vga.fs
index 53dcff0fb4..000000000001 100644
--- a/drivers/vga.fs
+++ b/drivers/vga.fs
@@ -246,14 +246,26 @@ : qemu-vga-driver-install ( -- )
 : qemu-vga-driver-install ( -- )
   mmio-addr -1 = if
     map-mmio vbe-init
   then
+  \ vgpu3d Phase 2: probe BAR2 control registers for passthrough magic.
+  \ VGPU3D_CTRL_OFFSET = h#4000, REG_MAGIC offset = h#08  → h#4008.
+  \ VGPU3D_REG_VERSION offset = h#0C                      → h#400C.
+  \ le-l@ reads little-endian 32-bit MMIO correctly on big-endian PPC.
+  mmio-addr -1 <> if
+    mmio-addr h# 4008 + le-l@        ( magic )
+    h# 56475033 = if                  ( "VGP3" — vgpu3d present )
+      mmio-addr h# 400c + le-l@      ( version )
+      encode-int " qemu,vgpu3d-ver" property
+      " true" encode-string " qemu,vgpu3d" property
+    then
+  then
   fb-addr -1 = if
     map-fb fb-addr to frame-buffer-adr
     default-font set-font

     frame-buffer-adr encode-int " address" property

     openbios-video-width openbios-video-height over char-width / over char-height /
     fb8-install
   then
 ;
